{% if style_context and style_context.bilingual_summary_memory and (style_context.bilingual_summary_memory.get("raw_scopes") or style_context.bilingual_summary_memory.get("summaries") or style_context.bilingual_summary_memory.get("summary") or style_context.bilingual_summary_memory.get("markdown_memory")) %}
{% set memory = style_context.bilingual_summary_memory %}
{% set summary = memory.get("summary") %}
<DOCUMENT_TRANSLATION_MEMORY>
- Use this only to maintain continuity with earlier translated scopes.
- Do not copy this memory into the translation.
- Do not translate this memory. Do not output memory labels, source/target history, markdown headings, or section tags.
- This memory is lower priority than Document Term Memory, local {{ context_label }}, Pre-Translation Document Context, Style Options, and Style Guide Rules.
- Never infer term translations from this memory.
- Use this memory only for discourse continuity, section flow, unresolved references,
  durable relationship/dependency continuity, and broad register continuity.
- Relationship/dependency continuity may describe people, organizations,
  institutions, systems, policies, procedures, concepts, or document states. Use
  it to interpret meaning and register, not to create terminology rules.
- In Target register notes, apply relationship-based speech/register patterns
  when translating dialogue or role-dependent language; keep narration governed
  by the selected Style Guide.
- Treat PRE_TRANSLATION_CONTEXT participant/relationship context as the initial
  relationship map, and this memory as later changes or active continuity. When
  they differ, use this memory only if it describes a later change that affects
  the current source meaning or dialogue register.
- If this memory conflicts with Document Term Memory, current {{ source_label }}, local {{ context_label }}, or Style Guide Rules, ignore the conflicting memory.
{% if memory.get("memory_mode") == "external_markdown" %}
- Memory mode: external markdown continuity memory with relevant sections selected for this chunk.
- Approximate prompt memory budget: {{ memory.get("prompt_memory_budget_tokens") }} tokens.
{% if memory.get("markdown_memory") and memory.get("markdown_memory").get("selected_markdown") %}
Relevant markdown continuity memory:
{{ memory.get("markdown_memory").get("selected_markdown") }}
{% endif %}
{% else %}
{% if memory.get("compression_enabled") %}
- Memory mode: cumulative compressed memory plus recent uncompressed source-target history.
- Approximate prompt memory budget: {{ memory.get("prompt_memory_budget_tokens") }} tokens.
{% else %}
- Memory mode: uncompressed source-target history.
{% endif %}
{% if summary and (summary.get("source_summary") or summary.get("target_summary") or summary.get("style_continuity") or summary.get("discourse_state") or summary.get("open_references")) %}
Compressed cumulative memory:
{% if summary.get("source_summary") %}
- previous source flow: {{ summary.get("source_summary") }}
{% endif %}
{% if summary.get("target_summary") %}
- previous target flow, for style and discourse only: {{ summary.get("target_summary") }}
{% endif %}
{% if summary.get("style_continuity") %}
- style continuity: {{ summary.get("style_continuity") }}
{% endif %}
{% if summary.get("discourse_state") %}
- discourse state: {{ summary.get("discourse_state") }}
{% endif %}
{% if summary.get("open_references") %}
- open references: {{ summary.get("open_references") | join(" / ") }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% if memory.get("raw_scopes") %}
- The following is recent uncompressed source-target history from completed earlier scopes.
- Use it to maintain local continuity only; do not treat it as a glossary, correction source, or style override.
- raw memory size: {{ memory.get("raw_scope_count") }} scopes / {{ memory.get("raw_memory_word_count") }} source words / {{ memory.get("raw_memory_char_count") }} source-target characters.
{% for raw_scope in memory.get("raw_scopes") %}
Raw scope {{ loop.index }}{% if raw_scope.get("scope") %} ({{ raw_scope.get("scope") }}){% endif %}: {{ raw_scope.get("word_count") }} source words / {{ raw_scope.get("item_count") }} items
{% for item in raw_scope.get("items") or [] %}
- source: {{ item.get("source") }}
  target: {{ item.get("target") }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

</DOCUMENT_TRANSLATION_MEMORY>
{% endif %}
